<div class="container">
    <section id="why">
        <div class="page-header">
            <h1><span class="blue-font">Odalisk</span> ?</h1>
        </div>
        <div class="page-body">
            <p>Odalisk stands for Open Data Live Score ChecKing !<br/>
			What is behind this words ? A basic process in order to help the Open Data movement to be more normalize.</p>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="span4">
                    <h3>Why <span class="blue-font">Odalisk</span> ?</h3>
                    <p>The Open Data movement began a long time ago, and the rush to open the data in cities, local areas, country is not the same in all the initiative. Some are very clean, some are very messy. For example, on a same platform, the date of creation is not in the same format.<br/>
					So that the movement be more normalize, we would like the platforms to respect some basic criterias.</p>

                </div>
                <div class="span4">
                    <h3>Objectives</h3>
                    <p>
					<ol>
						<li>Construct a list of robust balance criteria to define the openness of a platform</li>
						<li>Analyse the platform with this criteria</li>
						<li>Display a score of openness for the platform and its datasets</li>
					</ol>
					</p>

                </div>
                <div class="span4">
                    <h3>Workflow</h3>
                    <p>
					<ol>
						<li>First step : Download the pages</li>
						<li>Second step : Get all the information contained in the html</li>
						<li>Third step : Generate the score for the platform</li>
						<li>Four step : Make available all the information collected and calculated</li>
					</ol>
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

